    {
      "id": "field-driven-class-artifacts-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Field-Driven Class Artifacts",
      "position": {
        "x": -460,
        "y": -120
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Field-Driven Class Artifacts\n\nTwilite has outgrown the split where node classes are mostly ref/dictionary driven while edge classes are increasingly field driven. This task graph captures the plan to make both kinds of class artifact authorable through the same native language.\n\nOrder of work:\n1. finish the minimal shared contract work\n2. finish the remaining content/control/port composition decision in node primitive consolidation\n3. then move class artifacts onto the field-driven contract without working backwards from legacy examples\n\nWorking assumptions:\n- the larger graph ecosystem is revisable, not sacred\n- Twilite should set good examples instead of perpetuating legacy ones\n- classes should be ordinary graph artifacts, not exceptional runtime snowflakes\n- the baseline authoring language is `declaration`, `markdown`, `field`, `port`, and `view`",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
            "graphId": "markdown_class",
            "name": "markdown Node Class",
            "version": "0.1.0",
            "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
            "createdAt": "2026-02-24T20:05:15Z",
            "updatedAt": "2026-03-24T01:20:00.000Z"
          },
          "intent": "graph",
          "meaning": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "description": "Canonical markdown content node.",
          "defaults": {},
          "nodeDef": {
            "key": "markdown",
